DAILY ANNOUNCEMENTS
Six Flags Grad Nite tickets 








Due to the extension of the COVID-19 Social Distancing Guidelines we are canceling the Grad-Nite 2020 trip on May 16, 2020. There are two options for any students who have purchased Grad Nite tickets such as: 

Converting your tickets to “any day” tickets that you can use through the end of the 2020 season. 

Voiding the agreement and refund your payments. 


If you have purchased Grad-Nite tickets ahead of time you will need to email Dr Toulios 
, Mrs. Dergance 
, and Mrs. Whittinghill 
so we can work with Great America to process one of these two options. 

I again, understand your frustration on this situation ,and we are constantly working on preserving the safest and memorable experiences for you the class of 2020. 

We ask that you remain positive and know that traditions do not fade away but are solidified with one single spark, which is YOU our Argo Seniors! 





Student Council and Class Board elections 








Now is the time to run for student council and class board elections. Find your Class Board class in Canvas to find the forms and requirements for running for office. You have until April 9th to put your name in the hat for elections. 





New Changes starting Monday, January 13, 2020 








It’s a new year, a new semester and a good time to change bad habits. If you are one of those students who is always late to 1st hour, or even occasionally late, we have a few changes that we are starting on Monday that might help to get you going a little earlier. Our goal is to make sure you are in your first hour class on time. 

Starting Monday morning, all students who ride buses will be invited directly into the building, you will not be able to leave campus once you arrive on your bus. We encourage you to get your coffee and morning snacks in the cafeteria where lots of good stuff – including fancy coffees - are for sale. 

And the second change is that if you arrive to Argo after 8:00am you will be asked to throw away any purchased food or drink before entering the building. So, set your alarm for five minutes earlier if you have to stop for a donut or coffee before you get to school. 







